  <div class="row">
    <div class="col">
    </div>
  
    <div class="col-4">
      <!-- Button trigger modal -->
  
      <div class="menu">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#exampleModalCenter">
          Add a Child
        </button>
  
        <!-- Modal -->
        <div class="modal fade" id="exampleModalCenter" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="exampleModalCenterTitle" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered" role="document">
            <div class="modal-content">
              <div class="modal-header">
                <h5 class="modal-title" id="exampleModalLongTitle">Add a Child</h5>
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
                  <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
                </button>
              </div>
              <div class="modal-body">
                <form class="login" id="addChild-form" role="form" style="display: block;">
                  <center>
                    <h2>ADD A CHILD</h2>
                  </center>
                  <div class="form-group">
                    <input type="text" name="childName" id="childName" tabindex="1" class="form-control" placeholder="Name" value="">
                  </div>
  
                  <div class="form-group">
                    <input type="text" name="exercise_multiplier" id="exercise_multiplier" tabindex="1" class="form-control" placeholder="Exercise Multiplier (Ex: 50)"
                      value="">
                  </div>
  
                  <div class="form-group">
                    <input type="text" name="reading_multiplier" id="reading_multiplier" tabindex="1" class="form-control" placeholder="Reading Multiplier (Ex: 50)"
                      value="">
                  </div>
                </form>
              </div>
              <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" name="add-child-submit" data-dismiss="modal" id="add-child-submit">Add</button>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
  
        <button class="btn btn-secondary dropdown-toggle" type="button" id="dropdownMenuButton" data-toggle="dropdown" aria-haspopup="true"
          aria-expanded="false">
          Menu
        </button>
  
        <div class="dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right" aria-labelledby="dropdownMenuButton" color="#2D3B55">
          <a class="dropdown-item" href="/earnIt/1">Earn Time</a>
          <a class="dropdown-item" href="/spendIt">Spend Time</a>
          <a class="dropdown-item" href="/calculator">Calculate Bank Time</a>
          <a class="dropdown-item" href="/report/1">Report</a>
          <a class="dropdown-item" href="/help-FAQ">FAQ</a>
          <a class="dropdown-item" href="/logout">Log Out</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row justify-content-center">
    <h1 style="text-align:center">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

    {{!-- Accordion to hold the FAQ section --}}
    <div class="bs-example m-5">
      <div id="accordion">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-header" id="headingOne">
            <h3 class="mb-0">
              <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne">1. What is Time Bank?</a>
            </h3>
          </div>
          <div id="collapseOne" class="collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-parent="#accordion">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h6> Kids are spending so much time on their electronics and other wasteful activities. They do not spend enough time
                on meaningful tasks that build character, personable skills, etc. This app tracks the productive tasks that
                kids do in order to earn "bank time" that kids can spend when they want. The parents set the weight for each
                activity, so they can deem what they feel is important.
              </h6>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-header" id="headingTwo">
            <h3 class="mb-0">
              <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo">2. How do you earn Bank Time?</a>
            </h3>
          </div>
          <div id="collapseTwo" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-parent="#accordion">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h6>Wouldn't it be great if a kid spent more time doing important and constructive things in life rather than just
                playing with their electronics? Bank time is accumulated when a child does any productive task that a parent
                considers meaningful. The parent will set the weight of their child's productive task, and they will earn bank
                time at that specific rate of the weight (in percentages). For example, if a parent sets the weight of homework
                to 50%, a child will earn 5 minutes of "bank time" for every 10 minutes of "homework time".
              </h6>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-header" id="headingThree">
            <h3 class="mb-0">
              <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseThree">3. What is Productive Time?</a>
            </h3>
          </div>
          <div id="collapseThree" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingThree" data-parent="#accordion">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h6>Do your kids want to watch TV, play video games, or watch videos on their phones? This is the earned time that
                lets them do whatever it is that their heart desires.
              </h6>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <br>
        <br>
        <br>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
